cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NA 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a convex optimization approach for efficiently solving the multiclass SVM learning problem involving a sparse regularization and the multiclass hinge loss. Additionally, the paper may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as SVMs are commonly used in image classification tasks, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as SVMs are a popular machine learning technique, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper proposes two algorithms for solving the optimization problem, and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as the paper discusses the efficient numerical methods used to solve the optimization problem.
